"v.发出眩目光芒；怒目而视 【英】 v. 发出眩目光芒(to shine with dazzling light)；怒目而视(to stare fiercely or angrily) 【考】 cacophony : sound / glare : light(刺耳形容声音/眩目 形容光) v. 刺眼; 发出眩目光芒; 怒目而视 【参】flare(v /n 闪光; 闪耀) 【类】cacophony: sound = glare: light 刺耳是声音刺耳 = 刺眼是光刺眼 【记】glass + flare 闪耀；glass + stare，eye，戴着眼镜看人是能发出带着反光的眩目目光 【相关】flare也是对眼睛有刺激性的，只是是由fire 引起的，flare的开头是f,发音也象fire glare (v.)  late 13c., ""shine brightly,"" from or related to Middle Dutch, Middle Low German glaren ""to gleam,"" related by rhoticization to glas (see glass). Sense of ""stare fiercely"" is from late 14c. The noun is c.1400 in sense ""bright light;"" 1660s in sense of ""fierce look."" Old English glær (n.) meant ""amber."" Related: Glared; glaring."
